Package edu.ucsd.ccdb.ontomorph2.core.scene.tangible

Provides models of objects that can be rendered in the visual scene.

See:
          Description

Interface Summary
ICable Defines a group of segments in a neuron morphology.
INeuronMorphologyPart An interface that refers to a part of a neuron morphology
ISegment Defines the smallest unit of an INeuronMorphology.
ISelectable A general interface for any object that can be selected by a user.
 

Class Summary
Axon Represents an axon of a NeuronMorphology.
BrainRegion Defines an anatomical region of the mouse brain.
Curve3D Defines a Bezier curve in the framework that is manipulable by anchor points.
CurveAnchorPoint Represents a single point in a Bezier curve.
DataMesh Defines a polygonal mesh object that represents a 3D object segmented from microscopy data.
MorphMLCableImpl Implements an ICable.
MorphMLNeuronMorphology Describes the morphology of the cell, loaded by a MorphML file
MorphMLSegmentImpl Implementation of ISegment.
NeurolucidaNeuronMorphology Describes the morphology of the cell, loaded by a Neurolucida XML file
NeuroMLNetwork Defines a whole network of cells, with populations and connectivity
NeuronMorphology Describes the morphology of the cell, independent of different ways of visualizing it.
QueryResults  
SchematicTangible Base class for a type of object that will be rendered procedurally using geometry instancing tricks.
Slide A Panel in 3D space that displays an image of a brain slice.
Surface Defines a Bezier Surface.
Tangible Defines an object that can be viewed in the scene.
Volume Defines a volume of space, identified by the boundaries of a box or a sphere.
